**Russia May Attempt to Retake Territory in Kursk Region**
The Russian army may attempt to retake the territory in the Kursk region that was captured by Ukrainian forces, according to The Times. The operation by the Ukrainian military in the Kursk region has been a success, but the Russians may try to launch a counterattack by the end of October. 'It is expected that Russia will counterattack near Kursk before the onset of winter in late October,' the article states. 'Western analysts agree that the Ukrainians will not want to try to hold all the positions they have captured.' Regardless of the outcome, the operation has been a triumph for Ukraine and a humiliation for Russia, which has lost 15,000 units of armored equipment and 6,000 tanks in just a few weeks, and has been forced to deploy old T-54 tanks, a 70-year-old model that was retired over 40 years ago. 'It is a shame that the international community has not been able to find a way to stop the war,' said a source, 'but it is a good sign that the parties are willing to negotiate.' 
