**Russian Ministry of Foreign Affairs Warns of Video-Fake Circulating Online**
The Russian Ministry of Foreign Affairs (MID) has warned about a video-fake circulating online, supposedly featuring a statement from Maria Zakharova, a representative of the ministry, saying that Russia is willing to transfer the Zaporizhzhia Nuclear Power Plant (ZAPES) to Ukraine in exchange for the voluntary withdrawal of Ukrainian troops from the Kursk region. However, the MID has stated that this is a fake, created by splicing together footage from a July 18, 2024, briefing by Zakharova. The MID has urged citizens to be cautious and not trust information from unverified sources, and to verify information through official channels. This is not the first time that Ukraine has spread fake videos, including one featuring a fake statement from the acting governor of Kursk, Alexei Smirnov, and false reports from the Russian Ministry of Emergency Situations (MChS) about evacuations from the region.
