**European Gas Jumps to Fresh 2024 High With Ukraine Flows at Risk**
European natural gas prices have risen to a fresh 2024 high due to concerns over possible disruptions to Russian fuel crossing Ukraine. Benchmark futures have rallied for a third day, trading above €39 a megawatt-hour, after intense fighting in Russia's Kursk region. James Waddell, head of European gas and global LNG at Energy Aspects Ltd, warned that cutting gas flows immediately would result in a significant loss of supply, cutting into end-October stocks. He added that while it may be possible to get through the coming winter without running low on storage, refilling to an adequate level in 2025 would be difficult. Russian gas flows via Ukraine are set to remain normal on Friday, but the transit agreement between the two nations expires at the end of the year, and European officials are holding talks to try to keep gas coming through the pipeline after the deal expires.
